title: For Sale:  ★ M1 Garand - International Harvester (IHC) ★
postcontent:
US Government Issued (USGI) M1 Garand rifle - Manufactured by International Harvester Co. (IHC) for the US military in 1954. There are no import parts or marks anywhere on this rifle.  Performs and cycles flawlessly and is in very nice original condition. The IHC receiver has rare postage stamp markings. The original USGI issue LMR barrel (Nov. 1954) is shiny, in good condition and is accurate to the US Army's specifications at time of issue. (IHC did not manufacture barrels and LMR barrels are considered the best USGI barrels on Garands.)  The Bolt, Op rod, and Gas plug are all stamped IHC. All metal has original finish. There is no rust or pitting anywhere. The walnut stock has IHC lot number stamped inside barrel groove.  As you can see in the photos the stock is beautiful and does have evidence of US armory "eagle" cartouche as well as the "circle P" on handle. 

Included with rifle is 10 ammo filled enbloc clips with 80 rounds of 150 grain 30.06. Also included is a hard shell rifle case. 

M1 Garands manufactured by IHC are very rare and the most difficult to obtain of all four Garand manufacturers. To find one with this many original IHC parts is very rare. This Garand is not some piece of junk you find at gun shows. It is a complete functioning weapon that would still pass inspection at Parris Island. It is something that you will be proud to own and pass on down.  If you know an International Harvester tractor or truck collector please pass this along - I am selling for economic reasons and will entertain reasonable offers -Thanks.

title: For Sale:  Noveske NSR Keymod Customizable Free Float Handguard AR-15 Aluminum Black
postcontent:
Product Information
 Shop more Noveske products The Noveske NSR Handguard is the smallest, lightest customizable handguard available for the AR-15. The bare handguard without any additional rail sections mounted is only 1.48" in width. The continuous top rail allows you to mount iron sights, optics and any other accessories without additional rail sections. The KeyMod system allows users to customize the handguard with rail sections and direct mount accessories. The handguard is constructed of aircraft aluminum and finished with a Mil-Spec hard coat black anodizing. The handguard is secured to a steel barrel nut with 4 T25 Torx fasteners. Installation requires a 1-1/6" crows foot wrench (not included) for the barrel nut; standard AR-15 barrel nut wrenches will not work with this handguard system. The NSR will work with Heavy Profile barrels and a maximum size of .875" diameter low profile gas blocks when located under the handguard. SwitchBlock equipped barrels will work, when the gas block location is outside of the handguard. This is rail system is not compatible with gas piston conversions. 

The KeyMod accessories are easy to install from the outside of the rail. The system uses captured hardware so the accessory can be installed with a turn of a wrench, no more fishing backer plates down a forend or completely removing the handguard system to install or adjust rail sections and accessories as is common with other modular rail systems. The KeyMod rail sections have integrated recoil lugs and a v-block design which help properly align the rail sections and ensure that recoil forces and stress do not sheer the attachment screws. This attachment system is much stronger than most customizable systems on the market. KeyMod rail sections and accessories are not included with the handguard and must be purchased separately. 

NSR-13.5:
Length: 13.5"
Weight: 11 Ounces

Material: Hard Coat Anodized Aluminum Handugard, Steel Barrel Nut
1913 Picatinny Continuous Top Rail
Accepts KeyMod Rail Sections & Accessories (not included)
Requires 1-1/16" Crowfoot Wrench and Medium Strength Thread Locker (not included)

The Branded [ R-13 ] in large letters under each of the walnut grips was for that purpose.R=for Reagan 13=date it was manufactured
